---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service - BuildWorkPro" description="Terms of Service for using the BuildWorkPro platform." noindex>
  <Header />
  <main class="pt-32 pb-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">

      <div class="mb-12">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-brand-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Legal</p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-slate-900 tracking-tight">Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-400">Last updated: March 19, 2026</p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose prose-slate max-w-none prose-headings:font-semibold prose-headings:tracking-tight prose-a:text-brand-600">

        <p>These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your use of the BuildWorkPro platform ("Service") operated by BuildWorkPro ("we," "our," or "us"). By accessing or using the Service, you agree to be bound by these Terms.</p>

        <h2>1. Account Registration</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>You must provide accurate and complete information when creating an account.</li>
          <li>You are responsible for maintaining the security of your account credentials.</li>
          <li>You must be at least 18 years old to use the Service.</li>
          <li>One person or entity may maintain only one organization account (multiple user accounts within an organization are permitted).</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. Subscription and Billing</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>BuildWorkPro is offered at $79/month or $790/year (annual billing includes 2 months free).</li>
          <li>All new accounts receive a 14-day free trial with full access to all features. No credit card is required during the trial.</li>
          <li>After the trial period, a paid subscription is required to continue using the Service.</li>
          <li>Subscriptions renew automatically. You may cancel at any time through your account settings.</li>
          <li>Refunds are available within the first 30 days of a paid subscription. After 30 days, no refunds are issued for partial billing periods.</li>
          <li>We reserve the right to change pricing with 30 days' written notice. Existing annual subscriptions are honored at their original rate until renewal.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Acceptable Use</h2>
        <p>You agree not to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Use the Service for any unlawful purpose</li>
          <li>Share your account credentials with unauthorized parties</li>
          <li>Attempt to access other users' data or accounts</li>
          <li>Interfere with the Service's infrastructure or performance</li>
          <li>Reverse engineer, decompile, or disassemble any part of the Service</li>
          <li>Use the Service to send spam or unsolicited communications</li>
          <li>Upload malicious content, viruses, or harmful code</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Your Data</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Ownership:</strong> You retain full ownership of all data you enter into BuildWorkPro. We do not claim any intellectual property rights over your content.</li>
          <li><strong>License:</strong> You grant us a limited license to host, process, and display your data solely for the purpose of providing the Service.</li>
          <li><strong>Export:</strong> You may export your data at any time in standard formats (CSV) through the platform's export features.</li>
          <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> Upon account termination, your data will be retained for 30 days to allow recovery, then permanently deleted.</li>
          <li><strong>Backups:</strong> We maintain regular backups for disaster recovery, but you are responsible for maintaining your own copies of critical data.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Service Availability</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>We target 99.9% uptime but do not guarantee uninterrupted access.</li>
          <li>Scheduled maintenance will be communicated in advance when possible.</li>
          <li>We are not liable for downtime caused by factors outside our control (internet outages, third-party service failures, force majeure events).</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>To the maximum extent permitted by law:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>BuildWorkPro is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind, express or implied.</li>
          <li>We are not liable for indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages.</li>
          <li>Our total liability shall not exceed the amount you paid for the Service in the 12 months preceding the claim.</li>
          <li>We are not responsible for the accuracy of financial calculations, bid amounts, or pay application values generated through the platform. Users are responsible for verifying all financial data.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>7. Indemnification</h2>
        <p>You agree to indemnify and hold BuildWorkPro harmless from any claims, damages, or expenses arising from your use of the Service, your violation of these Terms, or your violation of any third-party rights.</p>

        <h2>8. Termination</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>You may cancel your subscription at any time through account settings.</li>
          <li>We may suspend or terminate your account for violations of these Terms with reasonable notice.</li>
          <li>Upon termination, your right to use the Service ceases immediately, but you may export your data within the 30-day retention period.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>9. Changes to Terms</h2>
        <p>We may modify these Terms at any time. Material changes will be communicated via email or in-app notification at least 30 days before they take effect. Continued use of the Service after changes constitutes acceptance.</p>

        <h2>10. Governing Law</h2>
        <p>These Terms are governed by the laws of the State of Florida, United States, without regard to conflict of law principles. Any disputes shall be resolved in the courts of Broward County, Florida.</p>

        <h2>11. Data Protection (GDPR)</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>If you are located in the European Economic Area (EEA), United Kingdom, or Switzerland, you may have additional rights under applicable data protection laws, including the right to access, correct, delete, or port your personal data, and to object to or restrict certain processing.</li>
          <li>BuildWorkPro processes personal data as described in our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.</li>
          <li>For data processing related to the Service, BuildWorkPro acts as the data processor and your organization acts as the data controller.</li>
          <li>A Data Processing Agreement (DPA) is available upon request for qualifying accounts. To request a DPA, contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@buildworkpro.com">privacy@buildworkpro.com</a>.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>12. Contact</h2>
        <p>For questions about these Terms, contact us at <a href="mailto:legal@buildworkpro.com">legal@buildworkpro.com</a>.</p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
